03:05:09,855 --> 03:05:12,960
In calming her, she was
calming her own heart.

3031
03:05:14,390 --> 03:05:17,360
As I watched her
becoming mother to herself

3032
03:05:17,395 --> 03:05:21,060
I felt my own long
motherhood ending.

3033
03:05:21,095 --> 03:05:23,960
I released what
I had held so long.

3034
03:05:23,995 --> 03:05:27,320
I celebrated the beginning
of her emancipation.

3035
03:05:28,190 --> 03:05:29,520
I let go.

3036
03:05:31,190 --> 03:05:34,390
Our work together
lasted 11 years.

3037
03:05:34,425 --> 03:05:37,420
Today Sybil lives peacefully
in a small college town

3038
03:05:37,455 --> 03:05:39,320
where she's
a professor of art.

3039
03:05:39,355 --> 03:05:40,990
There's not
enough time in the day

3040
03:05:41,025 --> 03:05:42,590
for her to do
everything she wants

3041
03:05:42,625 --> 03:05:46,160
but that time,
in every sense, is her own.

3042
03:05:47,090 --> 03:05:49,160
She tells me she's happy.

3043
03:05:49,960 --> 03:05:51,690
I know she's free.

3044
03:05:57,260 --> 03:05:59,820
colors of dreams

3045
03:05:59,855 --> 03:06:02,820
ribbons of rhyme

3046
03:06:02,855 --> 03:06:06,420
come out, come out

3047
03:06:06,455 --> 03:06:10,220
wherever you are

3048
03:06:10,255 --> 03:06:13,520
willows and winds

3049
03:06:13,555 --> 03:06:15,890
that whisper words

3050
03:06:15,925 --> 03:06:20,120
of a spring so near

3051
03:06:20,155 --> 03:06:23,390
a summer so far

3052
03:06:24,290 --> 03:06:27,790
mirror, mirror

3053
03:06:27,825 --> 03:06:31,590
in my mind

3054
03:06:31,625 --> 03:06:35,520
there's so much to see

3055
03:06:38,020 --> 03:06:40,960
walking through

3056
03:06:40,995 --> 03:06:44,960
your silver rooms

3057
03:06:46,120 --> 03:06:49,660
I remember

3058
03:06:50,290 --> 03:06:52,590
me

